post_text:
We understand that during this untraditional start to a school year many of you have questions. We just want to remind everyone that our Facebook Team only posts the information we are given, and beyond that we do not have specific answers to questions you may have.

If you have questions beyond what a post includes, you will need to call or email one of the offices or principals. We would love to answer all of your questions when you message us, but we simply do not have access to specific details or student data.

Thank you for understanding!

post_text: Westville School community I want to thank you for your patience and understanding during this very uncertain time. We are working on making plans for the next phase of our start up. We felt like the Purple - Gold schedule is a good way to open safely. We are surveying our staff today and will send out a survey for parents tomorrow. Our teachers and staff have been working very hard to make this startup as simple as possible. There have been set backs and unexpected delays and we want to apologize for those inconviences and misunderstandings. I would encourage you to reach out if you are having a problem or reach out if things are going well. A positvie message means alot in this trying time. But the main thing is to communicate with your students teacher and Principal and we can make things go better for you and your student. Reminder that we will not be in school on Monday, September 7 and Tuesday, September 8. More information will be sent out as soon as decisions are made. Thank you for your consideration. Jacket Pride!

post_text:
All junior high football players will practice tomorrow (August 31st) after school from 3:30-5:00. The 8th grade will stay until 5:30 to practice with 9th grade. We will keep all junior high football players after school on Thursday, September 3rd (game day). We WILL feed ALL
players before the game. Please note that we will be playing a 7th grade game mixed in with some 8th graders followed by a 9th grade game mixed with some 8th graders. This was originally scheduled to be a 7th grade game and an 8th/9th game. This is not able to happen because Lincoln only has six, 7th graders, while we have eleven or twelve, but with both teams mixing grades, it should allow us to have a game. We appreciate your patience.

post_text: Westville Public Schools made the decision yesterday after students were exposed to a confirmed positive case of Covid-19. In coordination with the Adair County Department of Health the decision was made to move to Distance Learning on the gold day because of the affected student(s). The district has suspended Cheer, Softball and Volleyball at this time. We will remain vigilant in our endeavor to keep our students safe and update the school community as these situations change daily. Our hope is to get every student to school everyday as soon as possibly safe. Thank you for your patience.

post_text:
Update: Our plan is ever changing, and with that in mind. Here are a few changes, Pre-K will start on August 20 or Aug 21 based on their day. To stay with less overall numbers on campus we are not allowing employees children attend on their off day. This will
help with small cohorts. This schedule allows us to start slowly and work our way up to all students at school. This is the safest way to return based on all of the recommendations and our unique campus with everyone using same cafeteria and other spaces. Our goal is to if our levels are safe to return the younger grades first. We will re-evaluate every two weeks. Our goal is to keep everyone as safe as possible and prevent outbreaks. Please be patient and understanding under this enormous undertaking. This is a trying time and very stressful for everyone involved so be kind to each other. We will get through this together.

post_text: After a zoom meeting today with the SDE and Superintendent Hofmeister, Westville schools will be re working and making changes to our Return to Learn Plan. The SDE has several recommendations for schools based on the number of cases in our county. We will still offer the same delivery methods but with changes to the mask policy for students. The mask policy will be based on SDE guidance provided. We will issue our revised plan early next week after gathering information from the SDE and the State board meeting. Thank you for your patience and understanding as things change very quickly.

shared_text:
Westville FCCLA
July 10 at 11:03 AM ·

Last year FCCLA Chapter Officer election process was changed to be more like District and State Officer Elections. Candidates have had to fill out an application, take an FCCLA knowledge test, undergo teacher and Advisory Board evaluations, and be interviewed. Each part being scored. With six high school offices available, the top eight scoring candidates will make the ballot. Junior High Officer ballot will be similar.

A ballot has been emailed to current FCCLA members. Voting will end Thursday, July 16 at 12pm. New officers will be announced Thursday afternoon.

Please check your emails. If you are a member and did not receive a ballot, please email Mrs. Alexander.

shared_text:
Reynalda Herrera Recruiting is with James Blackmore and 4 others at Army Recruiting Station Fayetteville SW, AR.
June 1 at 3:04 PM · Fayetteville, AR ·

Best of luck to two of our Future Soldiers Isaiah Smith and Randall Cope leaving today to ship off to Basic training‼️✈️ Both are recent graduates from Westville High School Oklahoma who enlisted under the Army Buddy Team option as 91B (Wheeled Vehicle Mechanic)for Active Duty. This is just the beginning for you guys and know that we wish you guys the best 💪🇺🇸

If you are ready for a challenge and would like to get information on how to get started let us know!

#GoodLuck #TheJourneyBegins #ShipDay #classof2020 #FutureSoldiers #ArmyLife #jacketpride

GIRLS- in grades 5th-12th for 2020-21 school year will be 8:00 a.m.-11:00 a.m. BOYS will be 12:00 p.m.-3:00 p.m. at the NEO Health Clinic. Parents must sign the consent forms. post_text: Free sports physicals for students that will be in grades 7th-12th next school year will be held on Monday, June 1st. post_text: A quick reminder for parents of JH and HS students. Please make plans for your child to come to the school between 8am and 3:30pm on their scheduled day next week. 7th and 10th grade students need to come on Monday the 18th. Eighth and 11th grade students need to come on Tuesday the 19th. Ninth grade students need to come on Wednesday the 20th. Twelfth grade can come on Wednesday the 20th and Thursday the 21st from 9am-3pm. Please bring textbooks, locks, library books, and parking decals to be turned in. If you are not able to come at these times, please contact the school to set up an arranged time to clean out lockers and check in materials. Thank you

shared_text:
Carson Community Bank
May 7 at 3:40 PM ·

Carson Community Bank is excited to announce our 2020-2021 Junior Board of Directors! These students will be the first Carson Community Bank board and the largest to date with 44 students; 19 from Stilwell, 16 from Westville, 6 from Keys, and 3 from Watts.

Students will participate in monthly meetings to learn financial literacy, successful habit development, leadership skills, and community stewardship. Members will receive a $500 scholarship in May 2021 to further their education.

Please help us congratulate our 2020-2021 Junior Board of Directors!

post_text:
Westville High School will join other HS nationwide on Friday to honor the 2020 Senior Class!

High schools around Oklahoma and across the country are banding together to honor the 2020 senior class amidst the coronavirus pandemic.

On Friday, April 10, at 8:20 p.m., Akin-Langley Field and outdoor stadiums around the state and country will turn on their lights for 20 minutes to show their appreciation for the senior class as part of the “Be the Light” campaign.

The lights are a beacon to show the Senior Class we are thinking of them and to remind them there will be a time where we will be all together once again.

The “Be the Light” campaign has been spreading across the nation as schools look for a way to celebrate their graduating seniors who are having their final memories in high school stripped away due to the Covid-19 virus.

Take a drive by the stadium during that time and honk to show your support. Please remember to adhere to social distancing protocol and stay in your vehicle.

Why the exact time?
20:20 for 20 minutes for the Class of 2020!

post_text: Last week Mrs. Miggletto sent an email to all Seniors (school email addresses) regarding the 5 local scholarship opportunities. These scholarships can be found on the District webpage: http://www.westville.k12.ok.us/o/district/page/scholarships-financial-aid--2 .The email contains directions on how to turn in the scholarships via email. If a student is unable to check their email or access the online applications, they should call Mrs. Miggletto 918-723-3181x1324 on Monday, April 13 between 11 am - 3 pm. or email dmiggletto@westville.k12.ok.us . Paper forms can be provided if needed. **The deadlines have been extended to April 30. Any Senior who plans to attend a college, ICTC or a vocational training should apply.

post_text: Westville Public Schools will be closing school under the order given by the Oklahoma State Board of Education today. We will be going to a distance learning program that will look different for each grade level and class. We will be delivering this education method starting April 6 and ending on May 8. Teachers are working hard to come up with a plan to provide every student with plan of study regardless of having internet or online services. More details will be coming in the following days and next week as we receive more guidance from the SDE. In the meantime we will still be having a grab and go meal service. This service will continue for the remainder of the school year. As of today March 25, Adair county has been put on the "shelter in place order" or "safer at home" order by the Governor because we have 2 confirmed cases of Covid-19 in Adair county. Please take the necessary precautions to keep you and your family safe. More information will follow in the days to come. Thank you, Terry Heustis

Oklahoma Hall of Fame at the Gaylord-Pickens Museum
February 21 at 6:35 PM ·

Registration for the 2020 Oklahoma Scholarship Competition is NOW OPEN! The deadline to register is Friday, March 13 at 5 p.m.

Each year, the Oklahoma Hall of Fame awards high school students with cash scholarships and tuition grants just for knowing all about Oklahoma! Students test their knowledge on Oklahoma history, geography and its people through an online exam, which will be administered Saturday, March 28. Each of Oklahoma's 77 counties has at least 10 scholarships available.

Ready to get your student signed up? Click here to register: https://bit.ly/2RNCuJL
